<article id="node-19551">
<h1 >1.1.S.258 Special widow</h1>
<p><strong>Note:</strong> This reference is for archival and historical purposes only. SSAct section 1214 was repealed by the <cite>Social Security Legislation Amendment (Parenting &amp; Other Measures) Act 1997, No.197</cite> and is no longer in operation.</p>
<h2>Usage</h2>
<p>This definition applied to all payments.</p>
<h2>Definition</h2>
<p>Until December 1997, a special widow was defined in section 1214(6) as a woman:</p>
<ul><li>who is getting <a href="../guide-social-security-law/acronyms#pps" title="Parenting payment (single)">PPS</a> because of the death of a man</li>
<li>who was legally married to the man immediately before he died</li>
<li>who was an Australian resident at the time the man died</li>
<li>whose husband was also an Australian resident when he died, and</li>
<li>who together with her late husband, were both members of the same couple (<a href="../guide-social-security-law/1/1/m/120">1.1.M.120</a>) when he died.</li>
</ul><div class="reference">
<p><strong>Act reference:</strong> <a href="https://www.legislation.gov.au/Series/C2004A04121" title="Social Security Act 1991">SSAct</a> section 7(2) An Australian resident is …</p>
</div>
